","options":["ghost echoes","sing-around","multiple echoes","wrap-around"],"correct":2},{"method":"UT","level":2,"question":"A 'normal' probe is one which","options":["operates at half wave resonance","operates at quarter wave resonance","has tungsten powder imbedded in its backing epoxy","introduces sound into a test piece at right angles to the surface"],"correct":3},{"method":"UT","level":2,"question":"The method whereby a discontinuity is detected and evaluated using reflected pulses.","options":["pulse-echo method","through transmission","bulk wave testing","crack tip diffraction"],"correct":0},{"method":"UT","level":2,"question":"The number of times per second that an ultrasonic transducer is excited to produce a pulse is","options":["determined by the crystal thickness","a function of the cable capacitance","the pulse repetition frequency","all of the above"],"correct":2},{"method":"UT","level":2,"question":"The gain or attenuation setting at which indications are assessed is the ________ level.","options":["reference","scan","threshold","bell"],"correct":0},{"method":"UT","level":2,"question":"Instrument settings which relate a reference echo of reproducible amplitude with which other instrument settings relating to a discontinuity echo are compared is the","options":["scanning level","threshold level","reference sensitivity","overall system gain"],"correct":2},{"method":"UT","level":2,"question":"Addition of suppression or reject to a display effectively","options":["filters out unwanted noise","reduces dynamic range","increases sensitivity","none of the above"],"correct":1},{"method":"UT","level":3,"question":"Sintering and grinding of transducer materials to obtain curved focusing (or de-focusing) surfaces can be obtained using","options":["rochelle salt","quartz","tourmaline","PZT"],"correct":3},{"method":"UT","level":3,"question":"The frequency of sound generated by magnetostriction is","options":["one half the applied alternating field","equal to the a