le probe's wedge is called a (an)","options":["cap","backing","anechoic trap","none of the above"],"correct":2},{"method":"UT","level":2,"question":"A calibration for horizontal linearity would check properties of the","options":["receiver amplifier","image unit (oscilloscope)","calibration block","probe"],"correct":1},{"method":"UT","level":2,"question":"The purpose of the 50mm diameter perspex insert in the IIW block is to","options":["check constancy of probe sensitivity","establish probe exit point","calibrate for range","both a and b"],"correct":3},{"method":"UT","level":2,"question":"An echo pulse width in steel determines","options":["a system's resolving power","time of flight","the far zone length","the frequency of the probe"],"correct":0},{"method":"UT","level":2,"question":"Pulse echo instruments without an image tube are","options":["not useful in NDT","not yet available","used for wall thickness measurements","not portable"],"correct":2},{"method":"UT","level":2,"question":"Electronic gates on the trace of a UT machine can be used to","options":["determine the presence of flaws","determine the amplitude of flaws","both a and b","none of the above"],"correct":2},{"method":"UT","level":2,"question":"When flaw echo signals are recorded so as to display a plan view of the test piece the presentation is called","options":["A-scan","B-scan","C-scan","D-scan"],"correct":2},{"method":"UT","level":2,"question":"Resonance testing techniques used for thickness determination use","options":["continuous sound waves","pulsed sound waves","Y-cut quartz crystal transducers","all of the above"],"correct":0},{"method":"UT","level":2,"question":"The purpose of a reference delay-line in an ultrasonic interferometer is for","options":["determining amplitude from a known reflector","accurate time measurements","eliminating near zone effects","eliminating dead zone effects"],"correct":1},{"method":"UT","level":2,"question":"Uniform and strongly adhering films of paint or oxi