 inspection will usually depend on","options":["probe size","nominal frequency","surface condition","sensitivity required"],"correct":2},{"method":"UT","level":2,"question":"In longitudinal wave inspection of the parent metal adjacent to a weld, minimum sensitivity is usually set such that","options":["it is 6 dB over the 80% FSH level for the appropriate side drilled hole","it is 20 dB over the 80% FSH level for the appropriate side drilled hole","backwall echo is 100% FSH in the absence of defects","none of the above"],"correct":2},{"method":"UT","level":2,"question":"When doing an ultrasonic weld inspection material thickness, weld preparation configuration, defect type and orientation are the main considerations for","options":["probe dimensions","frequency","probe angle","all of the above"],"correct":2},{"method":"UT","level":2,"question":"Gain corrections to compensate for attenuation are dependant on","options":["frequency used","grain structure of test material","pulse energy","a and b"],"correct":3},{"method":"UT","level":2,"question":"The IIW Block #1 is used to calibrate","options":["range","exit point","refracted angle","all of the above"],"correct":3},{"method":"UT","level":2,"question":"When calibrating an ultrasonic instrument for range, the maximum distance of interest should not be less than","options":["100 mm","200 mm","one half the horizontal scale","two thirds the horizontal scale"],"correct":3},{"method":"UT","level":2,"question":"DGS diagrams are used to establish","options":["defect depth","defect size","correct probe dimensions","beam divergence"],"correct":1},{"method":"UT","level":2,"question":"In the DGS (AVG German) system of defect sizing, the diagram relates to soundpath distance to the _________ to obtain the relative distance.","options":["probe size","near-field length","stand-off distance","depth of defect"],"correct":1},{"method":"UT","level":2,"question":"Where geometry permits in weld inspection, the distance you need to move the probe back from the weld to ensure 100% volume inspection is","options":["1/2 skip from the weld centre-line","1 full skip from the weld centre-line","1/2 skip from the edge of the heat affected zone","1 full skip from the HAZ edge"],"correct":3},{"method":"UT","level":2,"question":"During manual scanning, detection of obliquely oriented defects is improved by","options":["using a lower frequency","longitudinal wave inspections","adding swivel motion to the angle beam probe","all of the above"],"correct":2},{"method":"UT","level":2,"question":"Shear-wave probe angle for contact testing of plate between 10mm and 100 mm thick is","options":["45 and 60 degrees","determined by probe frequency chosen","dependant on plate thickness, position and nature of defect","none of the above"],"correct":2},{"method":"UT","level":2,"question":"Given a flat plate 25mm thick, the full skip range distance with a 60 degree probe is","options":["35mm","50mm","100mm","not possible to determine"],"correct":2},{"method":"UT","level":2,"question":"The half skip range on a 16mm thick plate with a 70% probe is","options":["24mm","33mm","47mm","64mm"],"correct":2},{"method":"UT","level":2,"question":"A defects' vertical extent is deduced by __________ motion of the probe","options":["lateral","traversing","rotational","orbital"],"correct":1}]$NDTA_SEED$::jsonb)
