re have been altered by heat of welding or cutting is called the","options":["fusion zone","heat affected zone","dead zone","twilight zone"],"correct":1},{"method":"UT","level":2,"question":"In a welding process using inert gas  as a part of the operation, the purpose of the inert gas is to","options":["react with the filler metal","provide a protective atmosphere over the weld puddle","increase the heat at the arc","harden the weld metal deposited"],"correct":1},{"method":"UT","level":2,"question":"The protrusion of weld metal beyond the toe, face or root of a weld is called","options":["overlap","undercut","pass","bead"],"correct":0},{"method":"UT","level":2,"question":"Another term for the welding phenomenon called \"suck-back\" is","options":["undercut","blow-through","concave rout","overlap"],"correct":2},{"method":"UT","level":2,"question":"Cracking occuring in the heat affected zone that does not usually extend to the surface of the metal is","options":["transverse cracking","underbead cracking","laminal cracking","post weld heat treatment cracking"],"correct":1},{"method":"UT","level":2,"question":"In tig welding the electrode manipulated by the welder is","options":["made of tungsten","not consumed","both a and b","none of the above"],"correct":2},{"method":"UT","level":2,"question":"When inspecting a curved surface with a contact probe it is advised to use","options":["circular probes","rectangular probes","large probes","small probes"],"correct":3},{"method":"UT","level":2,"question":"When inspecting rough surfaces, such as castings, coupling efficiency can be improved by","options":["using larger dimensioned probes","increasing receiver gain","using lower frequency probes","increasing damping"],"correct":2},{"method":"UT","level":2,"question":"For contact testing of thin steel plate (5mm) it is recommended to use shear waves at 80�.  A significant problem to contend with however is","options":["a large fraction of energy is converted to surface waves","i