nergy through a medium via __________.","options":["electron-electron collisions","strong nuclear forces","elastic forces","gravitrons"],"correct":2},{"method":"UT","level":3,"question":"In an elastic medium, particles vibrate","options":["about their position of rest","in shear mode only","in longitudinal mode only","according to Boyle's Law"],"correct":0},{"method":"UT","level":3,"question":"A material that is homogenous and exhibits the same elastic behavior in all directions is said to be","options":["a solid","a liquid","isotropic","plastic"],"correct":2},{"method":"UT","level":3,"question":"A material that is homogenous but does not exhibit the same behaviour in all directions is said to be","options":["anisotropic","a liquid","plastic","deformed"],"correct":0},{"method":"UT","level":3,"question":"The limiting factor for how short a wavelength may exist in an elastic wave is","options":["sound velocity in the material","the atomic or molecular spacing of the material","the PRF","the frequency content of the pulser"],"correct":1},{"method":"UT","level":3,"question":"Because MOST liquids do not possess this quality they do not support transverse waves.","options":["shear strength","plastic phase","density","inertia"],"correct":0},{"method":"UT","level":3,"question":"In a transverse wave, when maximum particle amplitude is reached, shear force is","options":["maximum","increasing","decreasing","zero"],"correct":3},{"method":"UT","level":3,"question":"The primary cause of plate waves occurring instead of pure surface waves is","options":["incident angle of sound","velocity of sound in the plate","thickness of the plate material","curvature of the plate"],"correct":2},{"method":"UT","level":3,"question":"In Lamb waves, the symmetrical wave is also called the","options":["plate wave","bending wave","dilational wave","Rayleigh wave"],"correct":2},{"method":"UT","level":3,"question":"In Lamb waves, the asymmetrical wave is also called the _______ wave.","options":["pl