ance frequency","fundamental frequency"],"correct":0},{"method":"UT","level":3,"question":"If a piezoelectric material is placed between (loaded) two materials that are sonically softer than itself it will vibrate in","options":["quarter wave resonance","half wave resonance","full wave resonance","continuous mode"],"correct":1},{"method":"UT","level":3,"question":"If a piezoelectric crystal is placed between (loaded by) two materials that are sonically harder than itself it will vibrate in","options":["quarter wave resonance","half wave resonance","full wave resonance","continuous mode"],"correct":1},{"method":"UT","level":3,"question":"If a piezoelectric crystal is placed between 2 materials, one sonically harder, the other sonically softer, it will vibrate in","options":["quarter wave resonance","half wave resonance","full wave resonance","continuous mode"],"correct":0},{"method":"UT","level":3,"question":"Although of lower amplitude, ultrasound resulting from the third harmonic can be utilized to an advantage for","options":["higher frequencies","higher dielectric strength","reduced fragility of crystals","all of the above"],"correct":3},{"method":"UT","level":3,"question":"Barium titanate, lead metaniobate and PZT piezoelectric transducers are","options":["polycrystalline","ceramics","sintered","all of the above"],"correct":3},{"method":"UT","level":3,"question":"When polarizing PZT ceramics for use as a transducer they are","options":["heated above the curie point","given a direct voltage of several thousand volts per cm","cooled while the voltage is applied","all of the above"],"correct":3},{"method":"UT","level":3,"question":"Ultrasonic image projection methods utilising interference effects result in images called","options":["a-scans","b-scans","c-scans","holograms"],"correct":3},{"method":"UT","level":3,"question":"If the pulse-echo method is used with a contact normal beam probe on steel (vel=6000m/s) and a flaw indication is seen at 3�sec on the scope, what is the distance to flaw?","options":["6mm","9mm","12mm","18mm"],"correct":1},{"method":"UT","level":3,"question":"Plate multiples on a CRT, when using the pulse echo method, are used for","options":["accurate attenuation determination","frequency determination","improving thickness determination accuracy","all of the above"],"correct":2},{"method":"UT","level":3,"question":"The purpose of the sweep generator is to","options":["form gate positions on the time base","form the baseline","determine the range on the CRT","all of the above"],"correct":2},{"method":"UT","level":3,"question":"Accelerating voltages used in CRT's for ultrasonic machines are typically","options":["500-1000 volts","2-12 kV","20-30 kV","1-2 MeV"],"correct":1},{"method":"UT","level":3,"question":"When testing thick specimens it may be desirable to","options":["increase pulse length","increase pulse energy","decrease PRF","all of the above may help"],"correct":3},{"method":"UT","level":3,"question":"When testing a thin specimen it may be desirable to","options":["decrease pulse energy","decrease pulse length","increase PRF","all of the above"],"correct":3},{"method":"UT","level":3,"question":"The type of amplifier most commonly used in ultrasonic machine receivers is the _________ amplifier.","options":["linear","logarithmic","superheterodyne","transient"],"correct":0},{"method":"UT","level":3,"question":"A disadvantage of a narrowband receiver in ultrasonic machines is","options":["non-logarithmic amplification ability","RF display is not available","pulses are broadened reducing resolution","none of the above"],"correct":2},{"method":"UT","level":3,"question":"The purpose of probe backing material is to","options":["provide damping to deduce ringing","absorb backward moving sound waves","provide mechanical support","all of the above"],"correct":3},{"method":"UT","level":3,"question":"Annoying signals resulting from unwanted radial mode oscillations of the piezoelectric crystal are reduced by