ings","vertical and overhead inspections","plastics"],"correct":2},{"method":"UT","level":3,"question":"In contact testing, the purpose of copper foil 20�m thick in a coupling oil layer is to","options":["reduce probe wear","change the refracted angle of the beam","improve transmission by acoustic matching","none of the above"],"correct":2},{"method":"UT","level":3,"question":"In steel, the range of wavelengths of ultrasound for routine inspection is","options":["0.1 to 1mm","1 to 3mm","3 to 6mm","6 to 10mm"],"correct":1},{"method":"UT","level":3,"question":"For a given probe, its sensitivity to a specific defect is","options":["dependant on the instrument it is used with","determined by AVG diagrams","constant under all conditions","none of the above"],"correct":0},{"method":"UT","level":3,"question":"Secondary echo signals from mode conversion of longitudinal waves to transverse waves off the edge boundary of a test piece can result in erroneous evaluations.  Signals will appear to be _________ than they actually are","options":["nearer","farther away","shorter","longer"],"correct":1},{"method":"UT","level":3,"question":"When testing the length of bar stock numerous echos can be seen on the screen after the first backwall.  These are","options":["secondary longitudinal echoes","mode converted transverse echoes","backwall multiples","any or all of the above"],"correct":3},{"method":"UT","level":3,"question":"When testing with angulated transverse waves, loses by scatter reflection","options":["increase with increasing angles of incidence","decrease with increasing angles of incidence","are unaffected by angle of incidence","depend only on surface roughness"],"correct":1},{"method":"UT","level":3,"question":"When using a refracted angle of 60� on a 50mm thick plate you get a defect signal at 120mm on the CRT (soundpath).  The standoff distance (distance from incident point along the surface to the point over the defect) is","options":["84mm","104mm","134mm","cannot 