ed of errors resulting in applying the AVG (DGS) method to","options":["materials other than steel","immersion testing","defects within the near zone","none of the above, Drs. Krautkramer have had 100% accuracy using the AVG system"],"correct":2},{"method":"UT","level":3,"question":"Trying to measure attenuation of a sample of INCO 910 you measure a 10cm thick sample by pulse echo and find it to have an echo 10 dB smaller than a 2.5 cm section.  The actual attenuation constant for INCO 901 is","options":["0.7 dB/cm","1.0 dB/cm","1.3 dB/cm","2.0 dB/cm"],"correct":0},{"method":"UT","level":3,"question":"Given INCO 901 has an attenuation constant for 5 MHz ultrasound of 0.67 dB/cm.  If you set the pulse-echo signal for the backecho from a 2.5 cm piece to 100% FSH; the back-echo from a 10 cm piece will be","options":["50%","32%","25%","12%"],"correct":1},{"method":"UT","level":3,"question":"If two very small spheres are placed beside each other in a ultrasound beam, the theoretical separation that can resolve them as two separate objects is","options":["one half wavelength","one wavelength","half the sum of their diameters","none of the above"],"correct":1},{"method":"UT","level":3,"question":"The fact that scattering always occurs in ultrasonic beam impinging on a defect of sufficient acoustic impedance difference from its surroundings","options":["implies there is no theoretical limit to sensitivity","allows resolution by interference","is the basis for acoustic spectroscopy","none of the above"],"correct":0},{"method":"UT","level":3,"question":"In order to extract wear flaw signals from incoherent noise signals modern technique utilize","options":["spectrum analysis","signal averaging","convolution","deconvolution"],"correct":1},{"method":"UT","level":3,"question":"The electronic apparatus used to selectively remove certain frequencies of a received ultrasonic signal is called a","options":["multiplexer","auto-correlator","cross-correlator","filter"],"correct":3},{"m