al","electrical","chemical","electromagnetic"],"correct":0},{"method":"UT","level":3,"question":"Studying the amplitude of successive multiple echoes to evaluate the quality of a material or bond is called the","options":["delta technique","decay method","DAC system","multiple echo technique"],"correct":1},{"method":"UT","level":3,"question":"The relationship between the incident angle of ultrasonic energy and the amplitude of the received echo is termed","options":["signal-to-angle ratio","angularity","acuity","directional sensitivity"],"correct":3},{"method":"UT","level":3,"question":"The difference in amplitude between the largest and smallest signals of measurable height capable of being simultaneously displayed on an A-scan is called","options":["sensitivity ratio","signal to noise ratio","vertical linearity","dynamic range"],"correct":3},{"method":"UT","level":3,"question":"An A-scan presentation has a minimum display height of 60mm.  The smallest signal that can be discerned is 2mm high.  Assuming the display is completely linear over the total height, the dynamic range is","options":["20 dB","29.5 dB","15 dB","44.4 dB"],"correct":1},{"method":"UT","level":3,"question":"A selected transit time range from which signals may be extracted for further processing is termed","options":["a gate","delay","a buffer","ram"],"correct":0},{"method":"UT","level":3,"question":"An acoustic frequency higher than the fundamental frequency, which results in a material of a given thickness to resonate is a(n) ___________ frequency.","options":["harmonic","beat","parallel","anti-resonant"],"correct":0},{"method":"UT","level":3,"question":"The relationship between horizontal distances along the time base and actual distances travelled by the acoustic beam is the","options":["range calibration","horizontal linearity","vertical linearity","echo repetition rate"],"correct":1},{"method":"UT","level":3,"question":"When ultrasonic testing the probe carrier follows the contours of the te