ible solution to lack of fusion in shielded metal arc welds","options":["decrease travel speed","increase electrode diameter","use proper bead sequencing","decrease welding current"],"correct":0},{"method":"UT","level":3,"question":"The solution to overlapping in shielded metal arc welding is","options":["increased travel speed","use proper electrode angles","use smaller electrode size","all of the above"],"correct":3},{"method":"UT","level":3,"question":"Lack of penetration in metal arc welding is not a result of","options":["too fast travel speed","wrong type of electrode","arc blow","poor joint design or preparation"],"correct":2},{"method":"UT","level":3,"question":"To correct the effects of magnetic arc blow in metal arc welding you could","options":["use alternating current","reduce welding current and arc length","change the location of work connection on the work piece","all of the above"],"correct":3},{"method":"UT","level":3,"question":"Allowing slag to run ahead of the welding arc in metal arc welding can result in","options":["cracking","inclusions","overlapping","poor penetration"],"correct":1},{"method":"UT","level":3,"question":"In tungsten inert gas welding, sticking or spitting of the tungsten electrode can result in","options":["porosity","inclusions","spatter","undercutting"],"correct":1},{"method":"UT","level":3,"question":"In the process of welding, if a welder provides \"slugging\" for his weld the result will be","options":["increased atmospheric protection","increased toughness","spatter is easier to remove","a welded joint not complying to design or specification"],"correct":3},{"method":"UT","level":3,"question":"Toe cracks occur in","options":["the weld metal at the end of a bead","the weld metal beginning at the weld toe","the base metal at the weld/base metal junction","none of the above"],"correct":2},{"method":"UT","level":3,"question":"The term upset is bulk deformation resulting from","options":["thermal expansion","improper tack wel