_-74 days","Tm-170 t_=129 days"],"correct":2},{"method":"RT","level":1,"question":"Given the ionizing field of x-rays at 2m is 2.5R/hr, what is the field at 5m?","options":["0.1 R/hr.","0.4 R/hr.","1.2 R/hr.","2.0 R/hr."],"correct":1},{"method":"RT","level":1,"question":"Given the field at 2.5m from and IR192 source is 2�Gy/hr, what distance could you approach before the field rose to 25�Gy/hr?","options":["0.21m","0.50m","0.67m","0.71m"],"correct":3},{"method":"RT","level":1,"question":"If a long weld is to be radiographed, it should be divided into roughly equal lengths, each of which is the maximum length of each radiograph less about 25mm.  The purpose of the 25mm is","options":["for identification markings or flashing","penetrameter placement","film overlap","hanger clip location"],"correct":2},{"method":"RT","level":1,"question":"The location along a welded seam is usually indicated on a radiograph by means of","options":["hard stamps","soft stamps","lead numbers","china markers"],"correct":2},{"method":"RT","level":1,"question":"In order to ensure good contact with the weld or casting being radiographed, ________ are preferred.","options":["film without cassettes","film in intensifying screens","lead masking beads","flexible cassettes"],"correct":3},{"method":"RT","level":1,"question":"Cassettes containing film are held in position for exposure by means of","options":["wooden supports","magnetic strips or springs","tape","any of the above ( whatever works)"],"correct":3},{"method":"RT","level":1,"question":"All electro-magnetic radiation with frequencies higher than _________ are considered to be \"ionizing radiation\".","options":["infra red","visible light","microwaves","ultraviolet"],"correct":3},{"method":"RT","level":1,"question":"Which is not a disadvantage of using gamma sources for radiography compared to x-ray?","options":["sources are large diameter so need long SFD","poor contrast","difficult to inspect thin steel","heavy shielding needed when not 