ifact, it is likely","options":["a piece of tungsten","hollow bead","slag","concavity of root"],"correct":0},{"method":"RT","level":3,"question":"Lack of fusion is usually oriented such that it is hard to detect but can be recognized by its","options":["density","linear nature","linear alignment in the direction of weld deposit","aligned disk shaped nature"],"correct":2},{"method":"RT","level":3,"question":"Undercut located by radiography is not usually considered a serious weld defect unless it is","options":["longer than the specimen thickness","deep and/or sharp","on the near (source) side","on the far (film) side"],"correct":1},{"method":"RT","level":3,"question":"Overlap is considered a severe weld defect because it","options":["forms a tight stress riser notch","is always long","is a corrosion initiation site","both b and c"],"correct":0},{"method":"RT","level":3,"question":"In radiographic interpretation of weld indications, the term icicles refers to","options":["overlap","tungsten inclusions","excessive penetration","high low condition"],"correct":2},{"method":"RT","level":3,"question":"A weld defect often seen on a radiograph in association with \"icicles\" is","options":["overlap","burn through","crater cracks","underfill"],"correct":1},{"method":"RT","level":3,"question":"Viewing a radiograph of single vee weld you see a long dark region centred in the weld.  It is continuous, about 4mm wide and not sharply defined.  The defect is likely","options":["hollow bead","concave root","under cut","excessive penetration"],"correct":1},{"method":"RT","level":3,"question":"Underbead cracking occurs in the","options":["root pass of a weld","heat affected zone of a weld","second last layer of weld passes","crater at the end of a weld bead"],"correct":1},{"method":"RT","level":3,"question":"Radiographic evaluation of porosity in castings may be termed as; microporosity, porosity or gas voids, the primary difference being","options":["size","source of gas","formation 