s","swinging field techniques","transformer amplifiers","connecting a welding machine in series to the bench unit"],"correct":0},{"method":"MPI","level":2,"question":"In MPI testing of irregular shaped objects using D.C. head shots, field strength is","options":["uniform at all surfaces","greater at small diameters or sections","greater at large diameters or sections","too convoluted to measure"],"correct":1},{"method":"MPI","level":2,"question":"Current distribution in a part MPI tested using prods depends on","options":["prod spacing","part shape and dimensions","resistivity of the part","all of the above"],"correct":3},{"method":"MPI","level":2,"question":"When you move half the prod spacing from the midpoint of the prod centre-line the field is","options":["maximum","minimum","much less than on the centre-line","equal to the field on the centre-line"],"correct":2},{"method":"MPI","level":2,"question":"Maximum practical prod spacing is about","options":["2 inches 5cm","4 inches 10cm","8 inches 20 cm","10 inches 25 cm"],"correct":2}]$NDTA_SEED$::jsonb)
