","level":2,"question":"The principle used in filtered particle inspection is","options":["the radiographic principle","Snell's law","Stokes law","differential absorption"],"correct":3},{"method":"LPI","level":2,"question":"Filtered particle testing would be used on","options":["ceramics","plastics","manganese","both a and b"],"correct":0},{"method":"LPI","level":2,"question":"Unlike normal liquid penetrant testing, filtered particle testing","options":["does not require penetrant","is used on porous material","does not require defects be open to the surface","all of the above"],"correct":1},{"method":"LPI","level":2,"question":"A high concentration of particles in the filtered particle inspection fluid will result in","options":["reduced absorption rates","excessive background","plugged pores","all of the above"],"correct":1},{"method":"LPI","level":2,"question":"Too low a concentration of particles in the filtered particle fluid results in","options":["failure to filter out at defects","excessive background","weak or poorly defined indications","plugged pores"],"correct":2},{"method":"LPI","level":2,"question":"For filtered particle inspection of cement the inspection fluid is","options":["water with a wetting agent","dilute HCl","penetrating oil","emulsifier"],"correct":0},{"method":"LPI","level":2,"question":"When performing a filtered particle inspection of unfired chinaware water cannot be used because","options":["it causes the clay to dissociate","it is too viscous","it is not viscous enough","water clogs defects"],"correct":0},{"method":"LPI","level":2,"question":"In filtered particle inspections, non fluorescent particles are","options":["never used","not as sensitive in operating ability as fluorescent particles","only used on complex shaped parts","only used on simple shaped parts"],"correct":3},{"method":"LPI","level":2,"question":"In filtered particle inspection pre-wetting refers to","options":["trapped moisture in insulators","wetting with a water suspended developer","application of water prior to applying inspection fluid","none of the above"],"correct":2},{"method":"LPI","level":2,"question":"In filtered particle inspections irrelevant indications","options":["are not easily confused to defects","are always fuzzy compared to defects","result from overlaps, scratches and drain marks","do not occur"],"correct":2},{"method":"LPI","level":2,"question":"The purpose of acid etching of a sandblasted or ground surface that was paint coated is to","options":["remove any paint that was missed","remove abrasives from flaw openings","remove smeared metal from flaw openings","all of the above"],"correct":2},{"method":"LPI","level":2,"question":"Bleed out width is","options":["directly proportional to defect width","inversely proportional to defect depth","proportional to defect volume","proportional to nothing"],"correct":2},{"method":"LPI","level":2,"question":"When a part undergoes several steps in fabrication, LPI or some from of NDT should be applied","options":["after the final operation","at critical stages of fabrication","after every operation in fabrication","none of the above"],"correct":2},{"method":"LPI","level":2,"question":"Aluminum sand castings are subject to","options":["shrink cracks","surface porosity and cold shuts","microshrinkage","all of the above"],"correct":3},{"method":"LPI","level":2,"question":"Die castings are not made of","options":["stainless steel","magnesium","aluminum","white metal"],"correct":0},{"method":"LPI","level":2,"question":"Gas turbine blades are usually made using the _______ method.","options":["sand casting","investment casting","die casting","fly casting"],"correct":1},{"method":"LPI","level":2,"question":"Forged jet turbine blades would be inspected using _______ penetrant.","options":["water-washable fluorescent","post emulsified fluorescent","solvent removable colour contrast","none of the above"],"correct":1},{"method":"LPI","level":2,"question":"Seams, laminations and 