"question":"A recommended limit for deterioration of fluorescence as compared to a reference is","options":["15%","25%","50%","85%"],"correct":0},{"method":"LPI","level":3,"question":"The glycerin breakdown test is used for water wash penetrants to determine","options":["degree of fluorescence","acid content","alkaline content","excessive water contamination"],"correct":3},{"method":"LPI","level":3,"question":"If sedimentation of 50% or more occurs in the glycerine breakdown test for water-washable penetrants it indicates","options":["excessive evaporation has occurred","contamination by heavy oil","excessive water contamination","both a and b"],"correct":3},{"method":"LPI","level":3,"question":"To obtain the specific gravity of a developer solution, the weight, in grams of a 100ml sample is","options":["the correct value","halved","divided by 100","multiplied by 0.1"],"correct":2},{"method":"LPI","level":3,"question":"Spot check penetrants in aerosol cans are not usually tested for operating control purposes because","options":["they are not as sensitive as fluorescent penetrants","the manufacturers guarantee quality level","they are not subject to contamination","none of the above"],"correct":2},{"method":"LPI","level":3,"question":"Usually, the single largest contributor to cost of a liquid penetrant inspection is","options":["penetrant","developer","emulsifier","labour"],"correct":3},{"method":"LPI","level":3,"question":"A symptom of conjunctivitis is","options":["a feeling of \"sand\" in the eyes","dizziness","double images","hyper thirst"],"correct":0},{"method":"LPI","level":3,"question":"Which condition indicates the outcome of the inspection of an overly conservative inspector","options":["a flaw is found when a flaw is present","a flaw is missed when a flaw is present","a flaw is found when no flaw is present","no flaw is found when no flaw is present"],"correct":2},{"method":"LPI","level":3,"question":"Probability of crack detection by LPI increases with"