roved by","options":["heating the test piece","adding water to the penetrant","increasing the viscosity of penetrant and or emulsifier","adding a wetting agent to the emulsifier"],"correct":2},{"method":"LPI","level":3,"question":"The diffusion of lipophilic emulsifier is stopped by","options":["consumption of reagents in the reaction","pre-determined time","water-wash removal of emulsified penetrant","none of the above"],"correct":2},{"method":"LPI","level":3,"question":"Emulsification time is not influenced by","options":["penetrant and emulsifier being used","surface conditions","type of developer being used","performance desired"],"correct":2},{"method":"LPI","level":3,"question":"Strippable film-type plastic developers","options":["are sprayed on with a non-aqueous solvent","provide permanent records of LPI indications","have very good resolution","all of the above"],"correct":3},{"method":"LPI","level":3,"question":"ASTM E43375 standard reference photographs for Liquid Penetrant Inspection does not","options":["classify type of surface discontinuities","classify characteristics of surface discontinuities","establish limits of acceptability","lend itself to be used as reference for acceptance standards"],"correct":2},{"method":"LPI","level":3,"question":"The result of a failed thermostat in a dryer causing overheating of an aluminum part can cause","options":["a delay while the part is cooled","excessive bleedout","no bleedout","overaging"],"correct":3},{"method":"LPI","level":3,"question":"\"Spot check inspection\" is based on","options":["results from \"Spot Check\" penetrant kits","small sampling of lots to determine lot quality","porosity counts","local examination of welds or castings"],"correct":1},{"method":"LPI","level":3,"question":"Increasing the temperature of penetrants too much above 40 degrees C. can result in","options":["degradation of dyes","gelling of constituents","decreasing viscosity","all of the above"],"correct":3},{"method":"LPI","level"