y variable"],"correct":0},{"method":"LPI","level":3,"question":"Strippable plastic film developers are a variety of ______ developers.","options":["solvent-soluble","water-suspendible","solvent-suspendible","all of the above"],"correct":3},{"method":"LPI","level":3,"question":"Solvents in strippable plastic film developers are","options":["used to decrease drying time","used to dissolve penetrant in flaws","both a) and b)","to be avoided"],"correct":2},{"method":"LPI","level":3,"question":"Standard fluorescent samples must be stored in cool dark conditions in glass or metal containers to prevent","options":["loss due to permeability of container","degradation due to chemical reaction","corrosive attack of the container","all of the above"],"correct":3},{"method":"LPI","level":3,"question":"Comparisons of LPI materials using the chrome plated brass panels are","options":["not possible","run on separate panels","run on the same panel using photographs for comparison","obtained from a single panel sheared in two halves"],"correct":3},{"method":"LPI","level":3,"question":"For LPI tests on surfaces where metal is smeared due to forming or surface abrasion it is tested by","options":["hot tank alkaline cleaning","solvent emulsion cleaning","ultrasonic cleaning","acid etching"],"correct":3},{"method":"LPI","level":3,"question":"Vapour honing would be used as a removal procedure for","options":["salt cake","rust","high temperature oxides","paint and varnish"],"correct":2},{"method":"LPI","level":3,"question":"Excessive bleedout of entrapped water washable penetrant may take","options":["less than 30 seconds","2 to 5 minutes","5 to 10 minutes","more than 30 minutes"],"correct":2},{"method":"LPI","level":3,"question":"A decrease in emulsification time with increasing penetrant contaminant is a result of","options":["excess heat of reaction","increased density","decreased viscosity","segregation"],"correct":2},{"method":"LPI","level":3,"question":"Solvent removal of post emulsifiable penetrant is used in the field","options":["when water is not available","with diminished sensitivity","only if flushing is permitted","never"],"correct":0},{"method":"LPI","level":3,"question":"Which of the following would not be a significant determining factor when deciding on an automated LPI system?","options":["type penetrant system used","volume of work","variations in test piece size and shape","cost of equipment"],"correct":0},{"method":"LPI","level":3,"question":"Generally, application of penetrant materials by electrostatic spray uses ________ of the material used by dipping operations.","options":["10%","50%","75%","110%"],"correct":0},{"method":"LPI","level":3,"question":"Hydrophilic emulsifiers are applied as a spray on foam","options":["on large irregular shaped parts","to speed up application","to reduce emulsification time","never"],"correct":0},{"method":"LPI","level":3,"question":"An \"air-knife\" is used in automated penetrant systems to","options":["excise defects","prevent contamination from previously applied solutions","cut off baked on developer","none of the above"],"correct":1},{"method":"LPI","level":3,"question":"For viewing in very critical inspections using visible dye penetrant, lighting intensity should be","options":["20 to 30 lux","400 to 500 edisons","100 foot candles","6000 angstroms"],"correct":2},{"method":"LPI","level":3,"question":"The changing from \"cone vision\" to \"rod vision\" is also called","options":["dark adaptation","photopic vision","scotopic vision","transvision"],"correct":0},{"method":"LPI","level":3,"question":"In tubular fluorescent blacklights, the actual source of black light is from","options":["cerium activated phosphor","tungsten filament","mercury gas","neon gas"],"correct":0},{"method":"LPI","level":3,"question":"The old weston 703 light metre was erroneously used to measure blacklight in units of","options":["footcandles","lux","watts per square metre","micro watts per square cm"],"correct":0}