n has a significant vertical vibration as it moves horizontally along and through the eddy current encircling coil.  How are defects detected through the resulting \"shaking\" noise?","options":["filtering","shock absorbers","spinning probes","gyroscopic mounted probes"],"correct":0},{"method":"ECT","level":3,"question":"Computer analysis of test results and signals are now common.  Which process would most likely be used to separate periodic defect signals from noise to determine periodicity of repetitive signals?","options":["initializing","fast fourier transform","averaging","standard deviation"],"correct":1},{"method":"ECT","level":3,"question":"Which of the following methods is used to determine coating thickness?","options":["x-ray and radioactive","optical and magnetic","ultrasonic and electromagnetic","all of the above"],"correct":3},{"method":"ECT","level":3,"question":"When the gap between two sheets of aluminium increases to a point past where no further change is seen on the eddy current instrument, what is being measured?","options":["maximum lift-off","maximum gap","metal thickness of upper plate","nothing is being indicated"],"correct":2},{"method":"ECT","level":3,"question":"When gap between two plates is to be determined the probe should be placed on","options":["the thinner of the two plates","the plate with higher resistivity","the plate with higher conductivity","both a and b must be considered"],"correct":3},{"method":"ECT","level":3,"question":"How was the 100% IACS value for annealed pure copper determined?","options":["it was arbitrarily assigned","by conversion from SI resistivity","by conversion from SI conductivity","from imperial units of resistivity"],"correct":0},{"method":"ECT","level":3,"question":"Which of the following, when added as an alloy of only 0.1% to copper will provide the greatest decrease in conductivity?","options":["zinc","phosphorous","iron","aluminium"],"correct":1},{"method":"ECT","level":3,"question":"Instruments us